      "claim_text": "Prior to the enactment of AB 1580, parents had to go through a rigorous process to freeze their children’s credit report."
    },
    {
      "claim_text": "The process to freeze a child’s credit report previously included a 60-90 day wait period and the provision of notarized identification documents to credit bureaus."
    },
    {
      "claim_text": "The new Child Identity Theft Law allows parents, legal guardians, or conservators to freeze the credit of children and incapacitated adults."
    },
    {
      "claim_text": "The new law allows for the credit freezing process to be significantly shortened."
    }
  ]
}
